<L>__{exterior river day}
<A>__{weighted down by his boots and clothing, schaefer struggles to stay afloat. gasping for air he ducks underwater, untying one of his boots. he surfaces, fills his lungs and dives again, releasing the other boot. he surfaces, strips off his shirt and pants and begins to swim towards shore, stroking with one arm.}
<L>__{exterior hunter's p.o.v. day}
<A>__{as he nears the edge of the precipice from which schaefer has fallen. the hunter in close pursuit does not hesitate but launches himself off the cliff in a spectacular leap, streaking downward towards the tops of the trees that grow out from the canyon wall. the hunter tears through the canopy of the first tree, the branches and leaves rushing past in a kaleidoscopic}
<B>__{blur.}
<A>__{the hunter bounds off of one branch after another, moving through the trees as an expert skier might negotiate a series of downhill gates. the hunter leaps free of one tree, bounds across twenty feet of open space to a large branch of a huge tree, affording a good view of the river below. from his vantage point, looking down at the windening, slowing expanse of river, schaefer is nowhere to be seen.}
